---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Layout title="About" description="What Why Is That, EU? is and how it works." canonicalPath="about">
  <style>
    h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .section {
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }
    .section h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .section p {
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      max-width: 60ch;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .section p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .section a {
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .cta {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      padding-top: 2rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .cta a {
      display: inline-block;
      background: var(--accent);
      color: #fff;
      padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      margin-right: 0.75rem;
    }
    .cta a:hover {
      text-decoration: none;
      opacity: 0.9;
    }
    .cta a.secondary {
      background: var(--surface);
      color: var(--accent);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
  </style>

  <h1>About</h1>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>What is this?</h2>
    <p>
      <em>Why Is That, EU?</em> is a knowledge base that explains EU directives and regulations in plain language —
      not just what they say, but why they were introduced, what political and social pressures triggered them,
      and what actually changed as a result.
    </p>
    <p>
      Most official EU sources tell you what a law does. This site tries to answer the question people actually
      ask: <em>why does this exist?</em>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Who is it for?</h2>
    <p>
      Anyone curious about the EU regulatory landscape — journalists, students, business people trying to understand
      compliance context, or citizens who want to know why their phone now comes without a charger.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>How are the entries written?</h2>
    <p>
      Each entry is drafted with the help of AI (Claude by Anthropic, or DeepSeek), then reviewed for accuracy.
      The AI is given analytical guidelines: identify the structural tensions, the coalition dynamics, the
      triggering event, and what specifically changed. Every statistic must cite its source inline.
    </p>
    <p>
      Entries include a provenance badge showing which model drafted them. The goal is transparency, not
      false authority.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Is it accurate?</h2>
    <p>
      We aim for accuracy but this is an AI-assisted knowledge base, not a legal reference.
      Entries may contain errors or be out of date. Always verify with official sources at
      <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">eur-lex.europa.eu</a>
      before relying on anything here.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>How many entries are there?</h2>
    <p>
      Currently 121+ entries across categories including Digital &amp; Data, Environment &amp; Climate,
      Financial Services, Labour &amp; Social, Agriculture &amp; Food, Transport, Consumer Protection,
      and Justice. More are added regularly.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Source code</h2>
    <p>
      The site is open source. Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>,
      full-text search powered by <a href="https://pagefind.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pagefind</a>,
      hosted on GitHub Pages.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/mih4ajlo/why-is-that-eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub →</a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="cta">
    <a href={base}>Browse all entries</a>
    <a href={`${base}search`} class="secondary">Search</a>
  </div>
</Layout>
